						<p><strong>Challenge:</strong> Powerful sustained winds and gusts across open plains with wind speeds regularly exceeding 40+ mph</p>
						<p><strong>Our Solution:</strong> Engineered wind-load calculations, reinforced post installation with deeper concrete footings, strategic panel design with wind gaps, and heavy-gauge materials specifically rated for high-wind agricultural areas</p>
					</div>

					<div class="weather-factor">
						<div class="weather-icon">☀️</div>
						<h3>Intense Sun Exposure</h3>
						<p><strong>Challenge:</strong> Extended periods of 100°F+ temperatures with no shade relief causing extreme UV damage and material expansion</p>
						<p><strong>Our Solution:</strong> UV-stabilized materials rated for agricultural use, expansion-conscious installation techniques, heat-reflective coatings, and materials specifically tested in Central Valley conditions</p>
					</div>

					<div class="weather-factor">
						<div class="weather-icon">🌡️</div>
						<h3>Extreme Temperature Swings</h3>
						<p><strong>Challenge:</strong> 50-60°F daily temperature fluctuations from cold foggy mornings to scorching afternoons causing material stress</p>
						<p><strong>Our Solution:</strong> Flexible fastening systems that accommodate expansion/contraction, material selection for temperature stability, and installation techniques that prevent stress failure from thermal cycling</p>
					</div>

					<div class="weather-factor">
						<div class="weather-icon">💨</div>
						<h3>Dust & Agricultural Debris</h3>
						<p><strong>Challenge:</strong> Constant wind-blown dust, agricultural debris, and abrasive soil particles affecting fence longevity</p>
						<p><strong>Our Solution:</strong> Durable powder-coated finishes, sealed fasteners, minimal moisture traps, and materials selected for abrasion resistance in dusty agricultural environments</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

